definition.value: A GDP-D-mannuronate in which the anomeric centre of the mannuronate fragment has alpha-configuration.
A methyl-branched fatty acid that is triacontanoic acid (melissic acid) substituted by a methyl group at position 28.
A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (11Z)-docosenoic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.
A methyl-branched fatty acid that is  undecanoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 10.

The cyclic ketal obtained by formal condensation of 1-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)ethanone with pentane-1,2-diol. A triazole fungicide, it is used commercially as a diastereoisomeric mixture on soft fruit (including apricots, peaches, nectarines, plums and prunes), nuts (including peanuts, pecans and almonds), mushrooms, and grasses grown for seeds.
A methyl-branched fatty acid that is pentadecanoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 14. It is a biomarker for rheumatoid arthritis.
A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (13Z)-docosenoic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.
A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-henicosapentaenoic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.
A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosapentaenoic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.
A glycol that is hexane substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 5.
A polyether that is a nine-membered polypropylene glycol terminated by an amino group at one end and a methoxyethyl termination at the other. A common crystallisation reagent.
A methyl-branched fatty acid that is heptadecanoic acid (margaric acid) substituted by a methyl group at position 16.
An oxo monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy as well as the 5-hydroxy group of nogalonic acid. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A O-butenoyl-L-carnitine  in which the acyl group is specified as crotonyl.
A methyl-branched fatty acid that is nonadecanoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 18.

An oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12-deoxynogalonic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A methyl-branched fatty acid that is  henicosanoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 20.
A monounsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (11Z)-18-hydroxyoctadecenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A methyl-branched fatty acid that is  tricosanoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 22.
A polyunsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (9Z,12Z)-18-hydroxyoctadecadienoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A methyl-branched fatty acid that is pentacosanoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 24.
A branched amino pentasaccharide comprising two galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetylglucosaminyl units linked beta(1->3) and beta(1->6) to a D-galactose residue.
A methyl-branched fatty acid that is heptacosanoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 26.
A  methyl-branched fatty acid that is nonacosanoic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 28.
A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is tridecan-1-ol substituted a methyl group at position 12.
A member of the class of  phenothiazines that is 10H-phenothiazine substituted by a 2-(dimethylamino)propyl group at nitrogen atom and a propanoyl group at position 2.
A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is  pentadecan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 14.
A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is heptadecan-1-ol substituted by a hydroxy group at position 1 and a methyl group at position 16.

A peptide zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino terminus of dapdiamide C; major species at pH 7.3. NB Although the relative configuration of the epoxide moiety has been assigned as trans, it has not yet been established whether the absolute configuration is R,R (as drawn) or S,S.

An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of 3-amino-N-(trans-3-carbamoyloxirane-2-carbonyl)-L-alanine; major species at pH 7.3. NB Although the relative configuration of the epoxide moiety has been assigned as trans, it has not yet been established whether the absolute configuration is R,R (as drawn) or S,S.
A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is  nonadecan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 18.

A very long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is  pentacosan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 24.
A very long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is  heptacosan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 26.
An ultra-long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is nonacosan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 28.
A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is hexadecan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 14.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 7-hydroxylauric acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is octadecan-1-ol (stearyl alcohol) substituted by a methyl group at position 16.
A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is icosan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 18.
A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is docosan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 20.
A hydroxy fatty acid obtained by hydroxylation of one of the two terminal methyl groups of phytanic acid.

An ultra-long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is dotriacontan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 30.
An ultra-long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is tetratriacontan-1-ol substituted by a methyl group at position 32.
